1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,916
- ( theme music playing )

2
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,083
- WHAT A PLEASANT SURPRISE.

3
00:02:13,166 --> 00:02:15,750
A FORTUITOUS OCCASION INDEED.

4
00:02:15,833 --> 00:02:18,083
JUST WHO I WANTED TO SEE.

5
00:02:18,166 --> 00:02:21,291
YOU'RE ANGRY WITH ME,
AREN'T YOU?

6
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:23,666
APPARENTLY YOU'RE
UNHAPPY THAT I FORCED YOU

7
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:26,541
TO KILL NICHOLAS
D. WOLFWOOD.

8
00:02:30,375 --> 00:02:31,375
- ( grunts )

9
00:02:33,208 --> 00:02:34,791
AAH!

10
00:02:37,166 --> 00:02:39,041
( pained groaning )

11
00:02:41,375 --> 00:02:43,583
- YOUR SCENE IS OVER NOW,
CHAPEL.

12
00:02:43,666 --> 00:02:46,833
NOW THE CURTAIN'LL RISE
FOR THE FINAL ACT.

13
00:02:46,916 --> 00:02:48,291
- ( groans )

14
00:02:48,375 --> 00:02:49,791
- ( rumbling )

15
00:02:49,875 --> 00:02:51,708
- ( gasps )

16
00:02:54,458 --> 00:02:56,791
- ( whimpering )

17
00:03:08,583 --> 00:03:12,000
- I'M CURIOUS.
WHY DID YOU COME HERE?

18
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:14,250
- I-- I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO LIVE

19
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:16,916
WITHOUT BEING ABLE
TO PAY OFF A DEBT.

20
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,916
- THAT'S NONSENSE.

21
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:22,750
ANIMALS RUN INSTINCTIVELY
WHEN THEY SENSE DANGER.

22
00:03:22,833 --> 00:03:26,125
BUT YOUR BEHAVIOR IS
COMPLETELY IRRATIONAL.

23
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:29,291
( laughs )
YOUR SACRIFICE IS MEANINGLESS.

24
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:31,625
YOU DON'T EVEN DESERVE
TO BE CALLED A FOOL.

25
00:03:31,708 --> 00:03:35,625
THE ONLY REASON THE HUMAN RACE
CAME TO POSSESS THE CAPABILITY

26
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:37,875
OF COMPASSION IN THE SENSE
OF MORALS

27
00:03:37,958 --> 00:03:40,833
WAS BECAUSE THEY SOMEHOW
MISTAKENLY BELIEVED THEMSELVES

28
00:03:40,916 --> 00:03:43,250
TO BE A SUPERIOR BREED OF BEAST.

29
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:44,916
THE MOMENT THEY TASTE
THE FEAR OF KNOWING

30
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,416
THERE'S A SUPERIOR BREED,
SOMETHING SEEMS TO TAKE CONTROL

31
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,125
OVER THEM EVERY TIME.

32
00:03:49,208 --> 00:03:51,625
AND FOR SOME REASON,
HUMANS ACT MERELY BY INSTINCT

33
00:03:51,708 --> 00:03:53,000
FROM THAT POINT ON.

34
00:03:53,083 --> 00:03:55,750
- THE CORNERED MOUSE
ATTACKS THE CAT,

35
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:58,041
EVEN KNOWING THE CAT
HAS THE UPPER HAND.

36
00:03:58,125 --> 00:04:01,250
- BUT THE CAT IS WISE
 TO THE MOUSE'S GAME.

37
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:04,250
THE MOUSE SEEKS DEATH
IN ORDER TO AVOID THE PAIN.

38
00:04:05,541 --> 00:04:08,083
- ( whirring, zapping )

39
00:04:08,166 --> 00:04:09,375
- ( groans )

40
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:12,250
- IMAGINE THE PLACE
BETWEEN LIFE AND DEATH.

41
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:13,916
- AAH!

42
00:04:18,666 --> 00:04:21,416
- YES, THE PAIN YOU FEEL IS
YOUR VERY ESSENCE,

43
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:24,833
THE ESSENCE OF THE CRUDE ANIMAL
KNOWN AS HOMO SAPIEN.

44
00:04:24,916 --> 00:04:26,791
- ( screams )

45
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:33,583
- GARBAGE-- ONLY GOOD FOR
CONSUMING RESOURCES.

46
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:36,875
( softly chuckles )

47
00:04:36,958 --> 00:04:39,625
- I UNDERSTAND.

48
00:04:39,708 --> 00:04:40,916
MASTER?

49
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,750
VASH THE STAMPEDE
WILL EXPERIENCE ETERNAL PAIN

50
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:44,750
AND SUFFERING.

51
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,875
- ( townspeople chattering )

52
00:05:03,166 --> 00:05:05,791
- HEY, LADY.
- HMM.

53
00:05:08,208 --> 00:05:10,416
- OH, MISS, MAY I HAVE 
SOME DOUGHNUTS, PLEASE?

54
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,416
- OH, YEAH?

55
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,708
HOW MANY DO YOU WANT?

56
00:05:12,791 --> 00:05:14,625
- 30 DOUBLE DOLLARS WORTH.

57
00:05:14,708 --> 00:05:16,916
OH, AND COULD YOU PLEASE
MAKE THEM FRESH ONES?

58
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,500
I DON'T WANT ANY DAY-OLDS, OKAY?

59
00:05:18,583 --> 00:05:21,458
- FINE, YEAH.
WHATEVER.  DON'T WORRY.

60
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:23,416
- ( Vash humming )

61
00:05:25,416 --> 00:05:26,416
( exhales )

62
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:28,083
A POPULATED CITY AT LAST.

63
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:30,333
SURE FEELS GOOD TO SEE
HAPPY PEOPLE AROUND AGAIN.

64
00:05:30,416 --> 00:05:32,125
IT'S A LUCKY LUCKY DAY.

65
00:05:32,208 --> 00:05:34,375
<i>BONJOUR!  JE T'AIME!</i>

66
00:05:34,458 --> 00:05:36,583
MM.  THAT SMELLS GREAT.

67
00:05:36,666 --> 00:05:38,000
WHAT A HEAVENLY AROMA.

68
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:40,166
SMELLS LIKE LITTLE CAKES
MADE FROM HONEY.

69
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:42,416
AND WITHOUT FURTHER ADO...

70
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,083
( laughs maniacally )

71
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:46,250
( chomping )

72
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:47,625
THIS IS INCREDIBLE!

73
00:05:47,708 --> 00:05:48,916
SUPER TASTY!

74
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,250
IT'S SO GOOD TO BE ALIVE!

75
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:52,666
- Boy #1: COME BACK!

76
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:54,375
- Boy #2: MOM SAYS SHE'S GONNA
BUY US SOME NEW TOYS!

77
00:05:54,458 --> 00:05:56,000
HURRY UP!
- I'M RUNNING AS FAST AS I CAN!

78
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:57,416
- Man: HAVE YOU BEEN
TO MAGGIE'S STORE?

79
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:58,833
SHE HAS NEW BULKS OF THAT NICE
FABRIC YOU LIKE SO MUCH.

80
00:05:58,916 --> 00:06:00,833
- Woman: I HAD NO IDEA.
SHE DIDN'T TELL ME.

81
00:06:00,916 --> 00:06:02,958
- Woman #2: THANKS A LOT!

82
00:06:03,041 --> 00:06:05,208
- I HAD THE OUTLAW.
 WHICH GIRL IS SHE?

83
00:06:05,291 --> 00:06:07,375
- NEVER MIND.
I'LL GO TELL HER MYSELF.

84
00:06:07,458 --> 00:06:09,458
- AT LEAST TELL ME HER NAME.

85
00:06:09,541 --> 00:06:12,125
- Man #2: IT TAKES THREE DAYS
TO GET THERE BY SAND STEAMER.

86
00:06:12,208 --> 00:06:13,541
FORGET IT!

87
00:06:13,625 --> 00:06:15,291
- TRUST ME, YOU GOT ABSOLUTELY
NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT.

88
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:18,458
IT'LL BE FINE.
- ALL RIGHT, IF YOU SAY SO.

89
00:06:18,541 --> 00:06:21,666
- ( chatter continues )

90
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,583
- Man #3: HA, I'M GONNA
GET YOU FOR THAT.

91
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:26,208
- WATCH WHERE YOU'RE GOING,
LINDA.

92
00:06:26,291 --> 00:06:28,166
- ( crying )

93
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,625
( voice breaking )
THESE ARE GOOD... 

94
00:06:32,708 --> 00:06:35,958
THESE ARE REALLY GOOD.

95
00:06:36,041 --> 00:06:38,416
WHY ARE THEY SO...

96
00:07:06,875 --> 00:07:08,583
- ( echoing )
VASH!

97
00:07:10,458 --> 00:07:11,791
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IT.

98
00:07:11,875 --> 00:07:13,500
WHY DO ALL THESE TERRIBLE THINGS
ALWAYS HAVE TO HAPPEN

99
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:15,416
WHENEVER YOU'RE AROUND?

100
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:17,583
WHY DID MR. WOLFWOOD
HAVE TO DIE?

101
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:25,875
( normal voice ) WHO IS HE?
YOU MUST TELL ME NOW.

102
00:07:25,958 --> 00:07:26,958
- YOU HEARD ABOUT IT.

103
00:07:27,041 --> 00:07:28,500
- YOU HAVE TO TELL ME.

104
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:32,291
- I AM TO BLAME.

105
00:07:32,375 --> 00:07:34,041
IT'S BECAUSE OF ME
THAT FRIENDS DIE.

106
00:07:34,125 --> 00:07:36,083
THEY ALL GOT INVOLVED
BECAUSE OF ME.

107
00:07:36,166 --> 00:07:38,041
I'M SORRY.

108
00:07:38,125 --> 00:07:40,208
BUT THAT'S WHY
YOU CAN'T STAY WITH ME.

109
00:07:40,291 --> 00:07:41,250
- ( exhales )

110
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:42,583
I ASKED YOU
AN IMPORTANT QUESTION,

111
00:07:42,666 --> 00:07:44,250
AND I EXPECT A DECENT ANSWER.

112
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:45,958
I NEED TO UNDERSTAND.

113
00:07:46,041 --> 00:07:47,708
PLEASE, FOR ONCE,

114
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:49,666
I NEED YOU
TO BE HONEST WITH ME.

115
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:55,750
- AS LONG AS HE LIVES,
I COULD NEVER DIE HONORABLY,

116
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:57,833
AS LONG AS KNIVES IS ALIVE.

117
00:07:57,916 --> 00:08:00,333
- WHO'S KNIVES?

118
00:08:00,416 --> 00:08:02,583
- MY BROTHER,
I'M SORRY TO SAY.

119
00:08:02,666 --> 00:08:04,083
- ( gasps )

120
00:08:04,166 --> 00:08:07,125
- ( soft rock music playing )

121
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:13,916
- ( inaudible )

122
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,416
- WELL, THAT'S IT.

123
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,250
NOW I NEED TO SPEND
A LITTLE TIME ALONE, OKAY?

124
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:51,958
- ( door opens )

125
00:08:52,041 --> 00:08:53,916
- AND BESIDES,

126
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,583
THERE'S A GIRL IN PAIN
WHO COULD REALLY USE

127
00:08:55,666 --> 00:08:57,541
YOUR SUPPORT RIGHT NOW.

128
00:09:00,708 --> 00:09:02,625
- ALL THIS TIME.

129
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:07,041
- Milly:
ARE YOU SURE?

130
00:09:07,125 --> 00:09:08,208
- HUH?

131
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:11,500
- I MEAN, DON'T YOU WANNA
FOLLOW HIM?

132
00:09:11,583 --> 00:09:14,458
- FRANKLY, I'M GLAD THAT NO-GOOD
TROUBLEMAKER IS GONE.

133
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:16,000
LET'S GET THE REPORT IN QUICK,

134
00:09:16,083 --> 00:09:18,291
AND GET THEM TO TAKE US OFF
THIS DETAIL ONCE AND FOR ALL.

135
00:09:18,375 --> 00:09:20,208
THERE'S SO MANY BETTER THINGS
OUT THERE.

136
00:09:20,291 --> 00:09:21,583
BESIDES, WE DON'T HAVE
ENOUGH LIVES--

137
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:24,083
- I CAN HANDLE IT, MERYL.

138
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:25,458
- BUT YOU--

139
00:09:25,541 --> 00:09:27,750
- UNLESS WE GO AFTER HIM NOW,

140
00:09:27,833 --> 00:09:30,333
THERE'S A GOOD POSSIBILITY THAT
WE MAY NEVER SEE HIM AGAIN

141
00:09:30,416 --> 00:09:31,500
IN THIS LIFETIME.

142
00:09:31,583 --> 00:09:34,750
IS THAT ALL RIGHT WITH YOU,
MERYL?  HMM?

143
00:09:34,833 --> 00:09:37,083
( giggles ) I'M COMPLETELY,
TOTALLY, PERFECTLY FINE NOW.

144
00:09:37,166 --> 00:09:38,875
IN FACT, I NEED TO
GET UP AND GO.

145
00:09:38,958 --> 00:09:40,666
AND BESIDES,
AS WE BOTH KNOW,

146
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:45,000
IF WE DON'T WORK,
WE DON'T GET PAID.

147
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:46,375
- MILLY.

148
00:09:46,458 --> 00:09:48,000
- ( sniffles )

149
00:09:48,083 --> 00:09:49,500
ALL RIGHT,
FIRST THING'S FIRST--

150
00:09:49,583 --> 00:09:51,541
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHICH WAY HE WENT?

151
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:52,791
- YES.

152
00:09:52,875 --> 00:09:54,875
- GREAT, THEN WE HAVE
NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT.

153
00:09:54,958 --> 00:09:57,458
I'LL BE READY
IN A FEW MINUTES.

154
00:09:57,541 --> 00:10:01,000
GATHER ALL OF YOUR THINGS
TOGETHER TOO, MERYL.

155
00:10:01,083 --> 00:10:02,708
MAKE SURE YOU DON'T
LEAVE A THING BEHIND,

156
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:04,250
BECAUSE WE WON'T
HAVE TIME TO COME BACK.

157
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:07,250
- ( crying )
YES.

158
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:08,625
OF COURSE.

159
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:12,208
- Boy #1:
HEY, THIS GUY'S CRYING.

160
00:10:12,291 --> 00:10:14,458
- YEAH, AND HE'S A GROWN-UP.

161
00:10:14,541 --> 00:10:16,625
- IS THERE SOMETHING WRONG
WITH THAT?

162
00:10:16,708 --> 00:10:18,791
EVERYONE FEELS LIKE CRYING
SOMETIMES.

163
00:10:18,875 --> 00:10:20,625
- WHY ARE YOU CRYING?

164
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:23,291
- A FRIEND OF MINE
WENT AWAY, AND I'M SAD.

165
00:10:23,375 --> 00:10:24,625
- WHY?
- BECAUSE--

166
00:10:24,708 --> 00:10:26,208
- HE DIED BECAUSE OF YOU,
DIDN'T HE?

167
00:10:26,291 --> 00:10:28,000
- ( gasps )

168
00:10:28,083 --> 00:10:30,625
- IT WAS YOUR FAULT. YOU'RE THE
ONE KILLED WOLFWOOD, AREN'T YOU?

169
00:10:30,708 --> 00:10:33,041
- YEAH, IF YOU HADN'T SWAYED HIM
WITH YOUR STUPID IDEAS,

170
00:10:33,125 --> 00:10:34,375
HE MIGHT HAVE HAD A CHANCE.

171
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:36,791
YOU KNOW THAT'S TRUE.
HE DIDN'T HAVE TO DIE.

172
00:10:36,875 --> 00:10:38,375
- WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

173
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:40,333
- Both: UH...

174
00:10:40,416 --> 00:10:41,625
- ( gasps )

175
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,750
- I DECIDED TO DO THIS
AS MY HUMBLE WAY

176
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:05,125
OF EXHIBITING GRIEF
AT THE LOSS OF A GOOD FRIEND.

177
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:06,458
HOW'D I DO?

178
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:07,750
- YOU AGAIN.

179
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:08,958
DAMN YOU!

180
00:11:09,041 --> 00:11:10,208
- ARE YOU GOING TO DRAW?

181
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:13,958
- PLEASE STOP.
DON'T DO IT.

182
00:11:14,041 --> 00:11:16,041
SOMEONE ELSE WILL DIE
IF YOU DO THIS.

183
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:18,500
ANOTHER ONE WILL DIE.

184
00:11:18,583 --> 00:11:19,916
- THAT'S RIGHT.

185
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,000
YOU CAN'T POSSIBLY DRAW.

186
00:11:22,083 --> 00:11:24,000
YOU SEEM TO THINK
YOU'VE NEVER KILLED ANYONE,

187
00:11:24,083 --> 00:11:26,458
BUT I'M AFRAID YOU'RE
VERY SADLY MISTAKEN.

188
00:11:26,541 --> 00:11:28,416
YOU'VE MANAGED TO FOOL
NO ONE BUT YOURSELF.

189
00:11:29,666 --> 00:11:30,916
YOU WANT TO BELIEVE THAT

190
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,458
BECAUSE YOUR HANDS AREN'T DIRTY,

191
00:11:32,541 --> 00:11:34,833
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T PERSONALLY
PULL THE TRIGGER,

192
00:11:34,916 --> 00:11:36,375
THAT YOU ARE INNOCENT.

193
00:11:36,458 --> 00:11:39,500
WHEN IN ACTUALITY,
YOU'VE KILLED COUNTLESS PEOPLE.

194
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:42,083
INCLUDING THE GUNG-HO GUNS
AND YOUR FRIEND...

195
00:11:42,166 --> 00:11:43,458
NICHOLAS D. WOLFWOOD.

196
00:11:43,541 --> 00:11:46,083
- I WAS FORCED TO DO THAT!
I HAD NO CHOICE!

197
00:11:46,166 --> 00:11:49,250
- EVERY TIME YOU MAKE THAT FACE,
IT'S STRANGE.

198
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:51,625
MY LEFT ARM BEGINS
TO SHAKE UNCONTROLLABLY,

199
00:11:51,708 --> 00:11:53,208
BECAUSE IT HAPPENS TO BE
THE VERY ARM

200
00:11:53,291 --> 00:11:56,416
THAT ATTACHED YOUR ARM
TO YOUR BODY.

201
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:57,416
- ( gasps )

202
00:12:01,041 --> 00:12:03,791
- I WILL BE WAITING
FOR YOU ON THAT HILL.

203
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:07,500
IF YOU WISH TO SHOOT ME NOW,

204
00:12:07,583 --> 00:12:09,708
GO AHEAD.

205
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,500
- ( Boy #1 groans )

206
00:12:13,583 --> 00:12:14,541
- ( gasps )

207
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:16,791
- WHAT HAPPENED?
MY HEAD FEELS FUNNY.

208
00:12:16,875 --> 00:12:18,291
- WHAT THE HELL?
- ( townspeople murmuring )

209
00:12:18,375 --> 00:12:19,250
- ( groans )

210
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:22,541
- HOW DARE YOU.

211
00:12:22,625 --> 00:12:24,125
HOW DARE YOU BE SO DAMN CASUAL

212
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:26,125
TO TOY WITH PEOPLE'S LIVES.

213
00:12:26,208 --> 00:12:28,583
- YOU'D DO THE SAME THING.
- ( gasps )

214
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:31,916
- YOU ALONE TURNED JULY
AND AUGUSTA TO RUBBLE

215
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,875
AND PUT A HUGE HOLE
IN THE FIFTH MOON AS WELL.

216
00:12:34,958 --> 00:12:37,583
YOU CAN DENY IT,
BUT YOU'RE A MONSTER.

217
00:12:37,666 --> 00:12:39,625
- Child:
MOM, WHERE ARE YOU?!

218
00:12:39,708 --> 00:12:41,291
- YOU AND HE ARE EXACTLY
THE SAME BREED.

219
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:42,875
- WHO DO YOU THINK YOU ARE?

220
00:12:42,958 --> 00:12:45,875
- I'M THE 11th GUNG-HO GUN,

221
00:12:45,958 --> 00:12:48,083
MIDVALLEY THE HORNFREAK.

222
00:12:48,166 --> 00:12:50,375
THE MAN WHO PLAYS 
THE GREATEST MUSIC

223
00:12:50,458 --> 00:12:53,083
ON THE GREATEST STAGE
OF ALL.

224
00:12:54,958 --> 00:12:56,250
IT'S TIME TO PLAY.

225
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:57,750
JOIN ME ON A NUMBER.

226
00:12:57,833 --> 00:12:59,666
WON'T YOU, VASH THE STAMPEDE?

227
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:01,208
- VASH?  THE STAMPEDE?

228
00:13:01,291 --> 00:13:03,166
- OH, NO.
NO WAY, IT CAN'T BE!

229
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,166
- ( townspeople screaming )

230
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:10,166
- ( rock music playing )

231
00:13:30,458 --> 00:13:31,916
- ( saxophone playing )

232
00:13:34,375 --> 00:13:35,458
- AAH!

233
00:13:38,291 --> 00:13:39,291
WHAT THE--?

234
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:47,041
SOMEHOW HE'S ABLE
TO SYNCHRONIZE THE SOUND WAVES

235
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:49,708
FROM HIS HORN WITH THE PHYSICAL
SENSATION OF PAIN.

236
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:01,250
AAH!

237
00:14:03,583 --> 00:14:04,791
- HMM.

238
00:14:04,875 --> 00:14:08,416
SYLVIA IS RESPONDING
RATHER WELL TODAY.

239
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:09,916
HEY, YOU WOULDN'T KNOW,

240
